snippet.textDisplay: I actually got this book (all four volumes!) for Christmas, and omg it’s actually hilarious. The reason Guanyin didn’t rename Sun Wukong is because his name had Wu in it, and so did the names she chose for Pigsy and Sandy. Sandy’s river was 3 million miles long and 300 miles wide. That’s bigger than the ENTIRE PLANET! I haven’t even gotten to Tripitaka’s introduction yet, and I’m already hooked.
